{
  "texts": [
    "To achieve this, each video undergoes a registration process, aligning it with the reference stenosis boxes using spatial translations within the video's spatial dimension.",
    "Before registration, every stenosis box is resized as a square with sides closest to 17.5 mm, using the real-life dimensions associated to the pixel spacing of every video, for standardization across examinations.",
    "The Discriminative Correlation Filter from the OpenCV Python library was used to perform registration 26.",
    "This approach performed better than similar registration methods and comparatively to approaches making use of AI for registration while being much faster 37.",
    "It tracks the spatial displacement of a segment of interest at a certain frame within a video in reference to the reference stenosis box and the frame was moved considering this displacement 37."
  ]
}